  "texts": [
    "For realistic TBG this symmetry is broken by intervalley Hund's couplings to the physical SU (2) s ×U (1) v ×U (1) c symmetry.",
    "Finally, there is yet another symmetry enhancement by tuning to the chiral limit and ignoring the dispersion: the U (4) × U (4) \"chiral-flat\" symmetry of rotations within each Chern quartet (see Section 4), which reduces to U (2) × U (2) when moving away from this limit back to the BM model.",
    "These three scales are illustrated belowU (4) C=1 × U (4) C=-1 (chiral-flat) → U (2) K × U (2) K ′ (BM) → SU (2) s × U (1) c × U (1) v (physical MA-TBG).",
    "(113)Of course, on a formal level the last symmetry is further explicitly broken to the exact microscopic symmetries.",
    "However, these are irrelevant to the experimentally accessible energy scales, and we therefore do not discuss this step further."
